text.tspan: If benefits of B's std > benefits of the FMVSS, and if
upgrading is appropriate, based on the incremental
benefits and costs, and applicable statutory criteria,
NHTSA tentatively determines B's std to have
greater benefits & issues proposal to upgrade the
FMVSS to level of B's std.
If benefits of B's std = benefits of the FMVSS,
NHTSA tentatively determines B's std to be at least
FE & issues proposal to add the requirements of B's
std to the FMVSS as an alternative compliance
option or to harmonize the FMVSS with B's std.
* Each of these steps includes engineering analysis
** "No" may simply mean that the data are insufficient
FMVSS = Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standards
pending availability of new data of
analysis. NHTSA may share the results
of its comparison with Country B.
PROCESS USED BY NHTSA IN COMPARING ITS VEHICLE SAFETY STANDARDS WITH THOSE OF ANOTHER COUNTRY (B)
AND DETERMINING WHETHER RULEMAKING IS APPROPRIATE
